## Customize
```python
from kwextractor.process.extract_keywords import ExtractKeywords
text = "tÃ´i thÃ­ch nghe cÃ¡c báº£n nháº¡c cá»§a Trá»‹nh CÃ´ng SÆ¡n"
fake_data = {
    "author": [
        "Trá»‹nh ThÄƒng BÃ¬nh",
        "LÃª Báº£o BÃ¬nh",
        "Phan Máº¡nh Quá»³nh",
        "Karik",
        "NgÃ´ Kiáº¿n Huy",
        "ChÃ­ TÃ¢m",
        "Trang Yue",
        "B Ray",
        "ERIK",
        "Emcee L (Da LAB)",
        "Badbies",
        "VÅ©",
        "SÆ¡n TÃ¹ng M-TP"
    ]
}
kw = ExtractKeywords(lan='vi', data_keywords=fake_data, return_group=True) # all parameters: data_keywords, lan, ngram, stop_words
print(kw.extract_keywords(text)) #{'author': ['báº£n nháº¡c', 'Trá»‹nh CÃ´ng SÆ¡n']}
```


## Features


| Feature | Description                                                                                                                                                       | Available at version |
| --- |-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------|
|ğŸ **Extract keywords from a sentence** | Extract keywords from a sentence. If the sentence has more than one keyword, the keywords will be separated by a comma. And empty if the sentence has no keyword. | âœ… v0.0.1 â‡ª           |
|ğŸ **Extract keywords from a paragraph** | Extract keywords from a paragraph and return a list of keywords                                                                                                   | âœ… v0.0.2 â‡ª           |
|ğŸ **Extract num-string from a sentence** | Extract num-string (number as text) from a sentence. Only return 1 number as a integer in a sentence.                                                             | âœ… v0.0.1 â‡ª           |
|ğŸ **Replace num-string with a number** | Replace num-string with a number in the sentence.                                                                                                                 | âœ… v0.0.1 â‡ª           |

## Development
### Install dependencies
```bash
